I&#39;ve been working with the Windows version of NEAT and I think I&#39;ve found
some problems.  Specifically, there appears to be extensive usage of
preincrement operators incorrectly.  For example, in CNeuralNet::Update() I
see this code block to prevent accumulation of values in the neurons:

for (int n=0; n&lt;m_vecpNeurons.size(); ++n)
    {
      m_vecpNeurons[n]-&gt;dOutput = 0;
    }

Another example is in CNeuralNet::~CNeuralNet():

for (int i=0; i&lt;m_vecpNeurons.size(); ++i)
  {
    if (m_vecpNeurons[i])
    {
      delete m_vecpNeurons[i];

      m_vecpNeurons[i] = NULL;
    }
  }

It seems to me that this usage is problematic, which I&#39;ve noticed in my use
lately.  Has anyone had any issues with this or noticed any problems?

-Kirk

